## Agent Capabilities (run from repo root)

- `make agents-init` ‚Äî Generate platform adapter files from agents.yml (`scripts/agents_init.py`)
- `make score` ‚Äî Self-score staged changes against 4-dimension rubrics (`scripts/score.py`)
- `make clean-imports` ‚Äî Remove unused Python imports with ruff (dry-run by default) (`scripts/clean_imports.py`)
- `make find-stale` ‚Äî Detect unused functions, classes, and variables (`scripts/find_stale.py`)
- `make commit` ‚Äî Conventional commit helper ‚Äî validates type(component): description format (`scripts/commit_helper.sh`)
- `make pr` ‚Äî PR creation with template pre-fill via gh CLI (`scripts/create_pr.sh`)
- `make new-task` ‚Äî Create a GitHub Issue for the agent backlog (agent-task label) (`scripts/create_issue.sh`)
- `make status` ‚Äî List open agent-task issues, filterable by component (`scripts/list_tasks.sh`)
- `make task` ‚Äî Execute a backlog task end-to-end in an isolated git worktree (`scripts/run_task.sh`)
- `make parse-error` ‚Äî Parse a Python stack trace and identify the DigiThings component (`scripts/parse_traceback.py`)

