## Shared Agent Surface

The skills, subagents, and slash commands below are defined once under `agents/sources/` and synced to every tool via `scripts/agents_init.py`.

**Subagents** (first-class in Claude Code; other tools should emulate the intent):

- `component-router` ‚Äî Maps a described change onto the correct component + reading list + test selector
- `dictation-normalizer` ‚Äî Reshapes rambling/dictated input into a structured instruction block; nothing lost
- `spec-writer` ‚Äî Emits GitHub Issue bodies matching .github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/agent_task.yml
- `pr-reviewer` ‚Äî Rubric-aware PR review mirroring docs/scoring/ dimensions
- `test-first-implementer` ‚Äî Red/green/refactor TDD loop bound to the component test command

**Skills** (prompted workflows ‚Äî invoke by name or when the trigger fits):

- `triage` ‚Äî see `.claude/skills/triage/SKILL.md`

**Slash commands** (Claude Code) / prompted workflows (other tools):

